      "telephone": "416-338-7255"
    },
    "isAccessibleForFree": true,
    "keywords": [
      "Arts/Exhibits",
      "Artisan"
    ]
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Event",
    "name": "Play Dead",
    "startDate": "2026-06-25T20:00:00-04:00",
    "endDate": "2026-06-28T16:00:00-04:00",
    "location": {
      "@type": "Place",
      "name": "Meridian Arts Centre",
      "address": {
        "@type": "PostalAddress",
        "streetAddress": "5040 Yonge St",
        "addressLocality": "North York",
        "addressRegion": "ON",
        "postalCode": "M2N 6R8",
        "addressCountry": "CA"
      },
      "geo": {
        "@type": "GeoCoordinates",
        "latitude": 43.766279895,
        "longitude": -79.414021087
      }
    },
    "description": "Play Dead invites you into a distorted world where the familiar twists into something wonderful and strange. Everyday rituals warp into surreal scenes, exposing the desperation that underpins our search for connection. In this gravity-defying universe, bodies collide and tangle, caught between beauty and menace — both intimate and unsettling.\n\nMontreal's People Watching crafts a vivid blend of acrobatics, movement, and high octane circus that magnifies the absurdity of the everyday. These moments, strange yet achingly familiar, mirror our own desire to hold on, like couples not wanting the last dance to end.\n\nHaunting and exhilarating, Play Dead captures the fragility, absurdity, and fleeting wonder of life lived on the edge of connection.\n\nLa Presse lauds the performance as \"Masterful fluidity, breathtaking…the circus of tomorrow\".",
    "url": "https://www.luminatofestival.com/play-dead",
    "image": "https://s3.ca-central-1.amazonaws.com/c3api-penguin-prod-toronto-storagestack-oc9o88-uploads/RYiOpZFXCMs8gaLgCLHG1A",
    "organizer": {
      "@type": "Organization",
